===Etymology===
From {{etyl|grc|en}} {{term|συνεργία||cooperation|lang=grc}}, from {{term|συνεργός||working together|lang=grc}}, from {{term|σύν||together|lang=grc}} + {{term|ἔργον||work|lang=grc}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|UK}} {{IPA|/ˈsɪnədʒi/|lang=en}}
* {{a|US}} {{enPR|sĭnʹər-jē}}, {{IPA|/ˈsɪnɚdʒi/|lang=en}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|synergies}} or '''synenergy'''

The joint energy of two or more agents or forces that is greater than the sum of their individual energies.

